            "Apply diminishing returns"
          ],
          "content": "## Production Function\nShows relationship between inputs and outputs.\n\n### Law\nDiminishing marginal returns.\n\n### Types\n- Short run\n- Long run\n\n### Managerial Use\nHelps optimize resources.",
          "examples": [
            "Adding workers increases output initially",
            "Overcrowding reduces efficiency"
          ],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Ignoring capacity limits",
            "Assuming linear growth"
          ],
          "qna": [
            {
              "q": "What is production function?",
              "a": "Input-output relation."
            },
            { "q": "Law?", "a": "Diminishing returns." },
            { "q": "Short run?", "a": "Fixed inputs." },
            { "q": "Example?", "a": "Factory workers." },
            { "q": "Use?", "a": "Efficiency." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
